TITLE: Judge denies request to lift ban on ASU students suspended for anti-Israel protests: report
SUMMARY: The U.S. District Court of Arizona denied twenty student protesters' lawsuit seeking to lift their suspension from Arizona State University.

TITLE: Patriotic Rutgers, UNC students push back against anti-America, anti-Israel agitators: 'Seeing a movement'
SUMMARY: Rutgers University students in New Jersey react to a show of patriotism on the school's campus Thursday, when exams were canceled due to anti-Israel protest disruptions.

TITLE: Man, 65, bitten by shark off South Carolina coast while spearfishing, Coast Guard says
SUMMARY: A 65-year-old man was spearfishing about 20 miles off the coast of Charleston, South Carolina, when he was bitten by a shark, the Coast Guard said.

TITLE: Drum major’s hazing left heartbroken mother wondering what really happened: 'He was beaten to death'
SUMMARY: Robert Champion, a Florida A&M drum major, was killed in November 2011. He was 26. His case is featured in Investigation Discovery’s “Murder Under the Friday Night Lights."

TITLE: Man charged with killing off-duty Chicago police officer denied pretrial release
SUMMARY: A 22-year-old man facing charges for the April 21 killing of off-duty Chicago officer Luis Huesca was denied pretrial release by a judge on Friday.

TITLE: Heavy rains over Texas have led to water rescues, school cancellations and evacuation orders
SUMMARY: The Houston area has been slammed by heavy storms, leading to numerous high-water rescues and officials urgently instructing residents in low-lying areas to evacuate.

TITLE: Arizona is boosting efforts to protect people from the extreme heat after hundreds died last summer
SUMMARY: To help prevent heat-related deaths, Arizona's new heat officer Dr. Eugene Livar said he is working with nonprofit groups and local governments to ensure homes have working air conditioners.

TITLE: Biden admin’s DOE investigating Emory University for alleged anti-Muslim discrimination
SUMMARY: Emory University is under investigation by the Department of Education's Office for Civil Rights after several groups claimed the school is discriminating against Muslim students.

TITLE: Three groups are suing New Jersey to block an offshore wind farm
SUMMARY: New Jersey is being sued by 3 anti-wind power groups to overturn an environmental approval for the Atlantic Shores wind farm project planned off of Long Beach Island.

TITLE: North Carolina student indicted for kidnapping, assault of teacher in viral incident, charged in 2nd attack
SUMMARY: A North Carolina high school student, 17, has been indicted by a grand jury on kidnaping and assault on a government official for two separate incidents involving teachers.

TITLE: NORAD detects, tracks 4 Russian military aircraft near Alaska airspace
SUMMARY: The U.S. military said it detected four Russian military aircraft flying near Alaska. NORAD confirmed that the aircraft stayed in international airspace.

TITLE: US employers scaled back hiring in April. How that could let the Fed cut interest rates
SUMMARY: US employers added a respectable 175,000 jobs in April, but still short of the estimated 233,000 jobs that economists had predicted.

TITLE: Fox News True Crime Newsletter: Confessions of a Russian sex spy, Kohberger video, 'justice' for pastor's wife
SUMMARY: Stay up to date with the Fox News True Crime Newsletter, which brings you the latest cases ripped from the headlines, from crime to courts, legal and scandal.

TITLE: Student grazed in head by stray bullet fired into Washington DC classroom
SUMMARY: A stray bullet struck a 17-year-old female student in the head Friday morning during a wild shoot-out outside her Washington D.C. school.

TITLE: 'Death to Israeli real estate,' 'Death to America' signs found on NYU property, NYPD says
SUMMARY: New York Police Department officials on Friday shared photographs of anti-Israel materials handed out at New York University including the phrases "Death to America" and "Long Live the Intifada."

TITLE: Death of South Carolina pastor's wife under investigation as her family warns of 'false' stories
SUMMARY: North Carolina officials are reportedly investigating the April 27 death of 30-year-old Mica Miller of Myrtle Beach. She was found deceased in Lumber River State Park.

TITLE: Sea lion numbers surge at popular California pier, reaching 15-year high
SUMMARY: San Francisco’s famed Fisherman’s Wharf district is seeing a surge in sea lions. The sea lions first started appearing at Pier 39 after an earthquake in 1989.

TITLE: Columbia partially reopens campus with desperate warning to faculty, students: 'Remains a target'
SUMMARY: Columbia University in New York provided an update to faculty and students about reopening its campus following weeks of antisemitic and anti-Israel unrest.

TITLE: Universities take measures to protect graduation ceremonies from anti-Israel protesters
SUMMARY: Universities including Michigan, Indiana and Northeastern are taking measures to ensure this year's commencement can proceed in the face of widespread anti-Israel demonstrations.

TITLE: Dallas to Tokyo flight canceled after Japan Airlines pilot's booze-fueled 2 am hotel rager
SUMMARY: Japan Airlines was unable to find a replacement pilot after a captain scheduled to fly from Dallas to Tokyo on April 23 had a night of raucous drinking with his flight crew.

TITLE: Anti-Israel protesters slammed as being 'gutless' for wearing masks to hide identities: 'Opposite of courage'
SUMMARY: Anti-Israel protesters are facing criticism for wearing masks and other face coverings while participating in demonstrations on American college campuses.

TITLE: NY DA Bragg probes police gunshot in Columbia University anti-Israel agitator response
SUMMARY: As NYC prosecutors move forward with charges against anti-Israel agitators who occupied a Columbia University building, they are also probing an NYPD officer.

TITLE: NYPD gives chilling update after 56 arrested at NYU, New School: 'There's somebody behind this movement'
SUMMARY: Officers from the New York Police Department went to New York University and The New School, where they ultimately arrested 56 people, with no incidents, between both schools.

TITLE: Boca Bash boat garbage dumpers face ‘imminent’ arrests as Florida authorities look to 'send a message'
SUMMARY: Charges are "imminent" against teens who threw heaps of garbage from a boat during the Boca Bash, the Florida Fish and Wildlife Conservation Commission said.

TITLE: Dramatic video shows driver racing towards protesters at Portland State University
SUMMARY: A dramatic video from Portland State University in Oregon, appears to show a driver racing toward a crowd of people on the campus.
